<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="81" type="conservation status">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Conservation status in Cameroon.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
<taxonomicName authorityName="C. Cusset, Adansonia, ser., 2, 14 (2): 274" authorityYear="1974" baseAuthorityName="Engl." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Podostemaceae" genus="Ledermanniella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Ledermanniella monandra" order="Malpighiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="monandra">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Ledermanniella monandra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has not yet been assessed for the IUCN Red List, but it was assessed in 
<bibRefCitation author="Onana, JM" journalOrPublisher="Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" refId="B66" refString="Onana, JM, Cheek, M, 2011. Red data list of the flowering plants of Cameroon: IUCN Global Assessments. Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew" title="Red data list of the flowering plants of Cameroon: IUCN Global Assessments." year="2011">Onana and Cheek (2011)</bibRefCitation>
. The taxon is known from one locality. The extent of occurrence and the area of occupancy are estimated at 4 km2 each. Due to habitat degradation and the continuous decline of vegetation cover in the area, extent and /or quality of habitat, 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="L." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="L. monandra" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="monandra">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">L. monandra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is currently reassessed as Critically Endangered. IUCN Red List category: 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Critically Endangered CRB2ab (iii).</emphasis>
</paragraph>
